eNCA's Govan Whittles is following this story. Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - The body of Khayalethu Magadla has finally been found. The six-year-old fell into an uncovered manhole in Dlamini, Soweto on 12 June while playing with friends. The search for him has taken close to three weeks. READ: Emergency services still searching for Khayalethu Magadla Several Emergency Management Services teams spent two weeks looking for him before eventually handing the search over to Joburg Water a few days ago. The boy’s family had told eNCA that they had accepted he would not be found alive but wanted to lay his body to rest.